  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nThe API does not return information for the next sync period's members when requested.\r\n\r\n## Version\r\n\r\n2.0.1\r\n\r\n## Present Behaviour\r\n\r\nThere appears to be a relatively low maximum lookahead for blocks, so for example if `head` is at 2425664 then the following occurs:\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ curl -H 'Accept: application/json' http://localhost:15200/eth/v1/beacon/states/2433024/sync_committees\r\n{\"code\":404,\"message\":\"NOT_FOUND: beacon state at slot 2433024\",\"stacktraces\":[]}\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Expected Behaviour\r\n\r\nIdeally the lookahead should be a full sync committee period, so that sync committee information can be retrieved for period _n_ at any time whilst in period _n-1_.\r\n\r\n",
